# Responsive layouts — museothyssen

## Single markup with Tailwind prefixes

Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` on the **same** node. Do not build two trees with `hidden` / `block` for the same content.

```twig
{# ✅ Correct — promo_banner #}
<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row lg:items-stretch">
  ...
</div>

{# ❌ Avoid #}
<div class="hidden lg:block">...</div>
<div class="block lg:hidden">...</div>
```

## Page container

In layout templates (`templates/page.html.twig`, regions), typical pattern:

```twig
<div class="layout-content mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
```

**SDCs do not set** site `max-w-6xl` unless the design requires a full-bleed block with its own inner (hero with `lg:max-w-[50%]` on a child, not on atoms).

## Flex and grid

- **Mobile stack → desktop row**: `flex flex-col lg:flex-row`
- **Card grid**: in paragraph/listing template, not inside `action_link`
- **Spacing**: `gap-*` on the flex/grid container; `px-6 py-12 sm:px-10 lg:pl-[clamp(...)]` when the design requires it (see `promo_banner`)

## Responsive images

- `sizes` on `canvas:image` props matching layout (`(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw`, etc.).
- Classes on `image.class` or wrapper `[&_img]:...` for Drupal render arrays.

## Drupal breakpoints

`dist/museothyssen_dist.breakpoints.yml` (generated on build) aligns with the dist theme; in Twig/CSS use the same Tailwind prefixes as in design.

## Storybook

Stories should look good at mobile and desktop viewports in the addon; no need to duplicate stories per breakpoint if Twig is already responsive.
